# Operational Maturity Model

Organizations typically progress through several stages.

| Level | Characteristics                                    |
| ----- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| 1     | Manual deployment and monitoring                   |
| 2     | Automated deployment with basic logging            |
| 3     | Structured observability and alerting              |
| 4     | Automated recovery and resilience                  |
| 5     | Continuous optimization and operational excellence |

The reference implementation is designed to support progression through each stage.

